Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the codebase. Let me create a detailed report:

## Comprehensive Codebase Analysis Report

### Project Overview
**Hey Chill** is a voice-first PWA (Progressive Web App) built with vanilla JavaScript, HTML, and CSS. It's a lightweight speech recognition client designed for hands-free voice input with two distinct interaction modes.

---

## 1. LANGUAGE SELECTOR IMPLEMENTATION

### Settings UI (HTML)
**File:** `/home/gem/project/index.html` (lines 137-142)
```html
<label for="lang-select">Language</label>
<select id="lang-select">
  <option value="">Auto-detect</option>
  <option value="en-US">English</option>
  <option value="zh-HK">Cantonese (廣東話)</option>
</select>
<p class="field-hint">Language used for speech recognition.</p>
```

### JavaScript Implementation (app.js)
**Language Retrieval (lines 174-177):**
```javascript
function getRecognitionLang() {
  return localStorage.getItem('recognitionLang') || navigator.language || 'en-US';
}
```

**Language Application (line 196):**
```javascript
